<section id="problem" class="border-t border-(--color-border) py-20 md:py-28">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
      <!-- Section label -->
      <p class="mb-4 text-sm font-medium tracking-wide text-(--color-accent) uppercase">
        The Problem
      </p>

      <h2 class="mb-8 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-(--color-text) md:text-4xl">
        Speed without direction
      </h2>

      <div class="space-y-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-(--color-text-secondary)">
        <p>
          Vibe coding has made building 10x faster. You can ship a feature in an
          afternoon that used to take a sprint. AI writes code, generates tests,
          scaffolds entire systems. The bottleneck isn't building anymore.
        </p>

        <p>
          The bottleneck is knowing <em class="text-(--color-text) not-italic font-medium">what to build</em>.
          Speed without customer signal means building the wrong
          things faster. You ship features nobody asked for. You miss the pain
          point that three different customers mentioned last week. You build
          based on gut and recent memory instead of structured evidence.
        </p>

        <p>
          North Star turns every customer conversation into a compass for your
          product. Record the call, get the transcript, see the insights. Feature
          requests, blockers, sentiment, action items — extracted automatically,
          searchable forever. So when you're deciding what to build next, you
          have the signal, not just the speed.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
